### Upload Test Endpoints for Ze da Fruta Backend
### 
### NOTE: You need to:
### 1. Start the server (npm run start:dev)
### 2. Login as a user to get JWT token
### 3. Replace {{token}} with actual JWT token
### 4. Replace file paths with actual image files on your system
###

### Variables (replace with actual values)
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = your-jwt-token-here
@productId = existing-product-id
@establishmentId = existing-establishment-id

### 1. Upload Profile Photo (Any authenticated user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/profile-photo
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="profile.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./path/to/your/profile-image.jpg
--boundary--

### 2. Delete Profile Photo (Any authenticated user)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/upload/profile-photo
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Upload Product Photo (Admin/Partner only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/product-photo/{{productId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="product.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./path/to/your/product-image.jpg
--boundary--

### 4. Upload Establishment Photo (Admin/Partner only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/establishment-photo/{{establishmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="establishment.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./path/to/your/establishment-image.jpg
--boundary--

### CURL Examples for Terminal Testing:

### Profile Photo Upload (bash/cmd):
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/upload/profile-photo \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN" \
#   -F "image=@path/to/your/image.jpg"

### Profile Photo Delete (bash/cmd):
# curl -X DELETE http://localhost:3000/upload/profile-photo \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN"

### Product Photo Upload (bash/cmd):
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/upload/product-photo/PRODUCT_ID \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN" \
#   -F "image=@path/to/your/image.jpg"

### Establishment Photo Upload (bash/cmd):
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/upload/establishment-photo/ESTABLISHMENT_ID \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN" \
#   -F "image=@path/to/your/image.jpg"
